  <section class="content">
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      The founder of Global Infrastructure Advisory brings a unique blend of engineering discipline, procurement
      expertise, and global program leadership. With experience spanning federal acquisition, donor‑funded development,
      and large‑scale infrastructure oversight, the founder has built a career focused on strengthening systems that
      support communities and national development.
    </p>

    <h2>Professional Journey</h2>
    <p>
      Over the years, the founder has supported infrastructure programs across the United States, Africa, the Middle
      East, and Southeast Asia — working with government agencies, international donors, and private sector partners.
      Their work includes PMO development, procurement governance, construction oversight, risk management, and
      monitoring & evaluation frameworks.
    </p>

    <h2>Leadership Philosophy</h2>
    <p>
      The founder believes that infrastructure is more than concrete and steel — it is the backbone of economic growth,
      public trust, and community resilience. Their leadership approach blends technical rigor with transparency,
      accountability, and a commitment to empowering institutions through tools, templates, and capacity building.
    </p>

    <h2>Vision for the Platform</h2>
    <p>
      This website is designed as a self‑growing ecosystem: a place where automation, AI dashboards, PMO frameworks,
      and global best practices come together. The founder’s long‑term vision is to create a platform that not only
      supports infrastructure delivery, but also contributes to workforce development and job market readiness through
