  <section class="content">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      A strong governance model ensures that infrastructure programs operate with clarity, discipline, and integrity.
      Our governance frameworks define how decisions are made, how risks are managed, how performance is monitored, and
      how accountability is maintained across complex, multi‑stakeholder environments.
    </p>

    <h2>Core Governance Components</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Decision Rights:</strong> Clear authority levels, approval thresholds, and escalation paths.</li>
      <li><strong>Oversight Structures:</strong> Committees, review boards, and independent verification bodies.</li>
      <li><strong>Policies & Procedures:</strong> Standardized rules for procurement, risk, reporting, and compliance.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency Mechanisms:</strong> Documentation, audit trails, and public reporting tools.</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Governance:</strong> KPIs, dashboards, and leadership scorecards.</li>
      <li><strong>Risk Governance:</strong> Enterprise risk frameworks and mitigation oversight.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>AI‑Enabled Governance Intelligence</h2>
    <p>
      Your platform integrates automation and AI to strengthen governance across all levels. These tools support:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Automated compliance checks and governance alerts</li>
      <li>Predictive analytics for decision‑making</li>
      <li>Cross‑project governance benchmarking</li>
      <li>Real‑time dashboards for leadership and donors</li>
      <li>Document and photo‑based verification workflows</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Integration With PMO, Risk, M&E, and Oversight Systems</h2>
    <p>
      Governance is not a standalone function — it is the backbone that connects PMO systems, risk management,
      construction oversight, and M&E. Your governance model ensures that all systems operate in harmony, with shared
      data, aligned processes, and unified reporting.
    </p>

    <h2>Future Expansion: Global Governance Exchange</h2>
    <p>
      As your platform grows, we are developing a global governance exchange where:
    </p>

